<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The standard way to do bribes (not legal advic=
e!) is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You work for some big international c=
ompany.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You want to win a lucrativ=
e government contract in some foreign country.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">You sign a deal with some well-connected partner company in th=
e foreign country,=C2=A0in which you pay the partner company a bunch of cas=
h, and the partner company agrees to provide you with some sort of vague se=
rvices connected to the contract.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
The foreign partner company takes the cash that you paid it, keeps some for=
 itself, and pays the rest directly to the foreign official in charge of aw=
arding the contract.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The official =
awards the contract to you.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The co=
ntract is lucrative enough to cover the cost of the bribes, and the foreign=
 partner company=E2=80=99s cut, and your company=E2=80=99s profit margin, a=
nd your bonus.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are various accounting issues; you will =
want your payments to the foreign partner company to look plausible. (=E2=
=80=9CEngineering services=E2=80=9D is probably better than =E2=80=9Cconsul=
ting,=E2=80=9D which is probably better than =E2=80=9Cbribes,=E2=80=9D whic=
h is probably better than =E2=80=9Cchickens, wink wink.=E2=80=9D)=C2=A0But =
there are also <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/298=
